quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  107,1,Do you see the one who denies religion and does not recognize Allah nor His control and government of all events
  107,2,Such is he who ill-treats the orphan
  107,3,And discourages aid to the indigent faint soul past corporal toil
  107,4,"And so, Woe to those who make great pretences to religion and their hearts' ears to exhortation are not inclined"
  107,5,"Who are oblivious of their act of worship, and when they perform it, their countenances reflect and speak absence of mind"
  107,6,"Who cultivate pretence and they, themselves, are empty of all good"
  107,7,Their malevolence prevents benevolence and proves an occasion of so much discontent